SUMMARY:Chipper's Preschool & Sensory Skate
DESCRIPTION:Get some morning wiggles out at Oaks Park Roller Rink where kiddos can skate at their own pace during their special toddler skate time on Tuesdays and Wednesdays from 10 AM-11:30 AM. \nEnjoy skating fun\, snack time\, and a visit with Chipper the Squirrel. As part of this specialty session\, Coach Amy teaches a 15-minute group skating lesson that introduces young kids to the principles of body movement while helping toddlers learn to follow directions through fun games. \nSensory Skate\nNow offering a special sensory-sensitive skate time during the Wednesday Preschool Skate. Music volumes will be reduced\, disco lights turned off\, and a quiet sensory play space will be provided. Sensory Skate is open to all children 10 and younger and their families.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/chippers-preschool-sensory-skate/2026-03-17/
LOCATION:Oaks Amusement Park\, 7805 SE Oaks Park Way\, Portland\, OR\, 97202
CATEGORIES:Active,Kids Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/preschool-skate-oaks-park-1.png
END:VEVENT
