SUMMARY:Making Waves - The Science of Music and Sound
DESCRIPTION:Making Waves – The Science of Music and Sound \nWhat is sound? How do our ears and brains hear music? How do different types of instruments produce different sounds? \nThese and other questions are answered when music meets science in this fun\, interactive program complete with hands-on experiments. (Grades K-8) \nRegister Today! \n\n\nMar 17th\, 10 am – Noon \n\n\nSliding scale $10-12 per student \n\n\nStudent capacity: 60 \n\n\nFine arts\, STEM \n\n\n  \nAt Ethos Music Center we believe all young people deserve access to the benefits of music education.  \nEthos offers unique and enriching field trip programs for preschool through high school-aged students. Our daytime programs are great for homeschoolers\, school classes\, community organizations\, Scout groups\, and clubs. We offer both on-site and off-site programming on a variety of fun and educational topics\, and can also customize programming to meet the needs and interests of students. For more information or to request a customized field trip for your group\, send us an email at info@ethos.org.  We can design programs onsite at Ethos or offsite at yours. \nEthos committed to providing culturally-responsive\, affordable programming in an environment that is safe and supportive for all Oregon’s young musicians. \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/making-waves-the-science-of-music-and-sound/
LOCATION:Ethos Music Center\, N Killingsworth\, Portland\, O\, 97217\, United States
CATEGORIES:Kids Calendar,Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/Science-of-Music-cropped-scaled.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Ethos Music Center":MAILTO:info@ethos.org
END:VEVENT
